Modelled North Pacific change due to AMOC slow-down. 
   a Winter SST anomalies of HS-1 to the LGM; 
   b The coeval winter SSS anomalies; 
   c The coeval wMLD anomalies; 
   d The coeval change in winter atmospheric circulation. In 
   d, the shading colours show net precipitation change, and the green and purple lines describing positive and negative change in sea level pressures, respectively. Here, the negative values of sea level pressure change over the subarctic Pacific Ocean imply an intensified Aleutian Low system in HS-1
